n style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">clarified. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> Many believe that by taking responsibility for clearing snow and ice they become liable to prosecution for any resulting injuries or accidents on the area that they have cleared. This is stopping communit</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ies helping themselves. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">2.6</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Should further action or powers be taken by central government or its agencies to assure salt supplies or winter resilience generally?</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Prepare for the worst and have salt s</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">tock levels </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">to cover this so that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">sto</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">cks don’t redu</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">ce</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> to the levels they fell to last winter.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Existing</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> powers, good planning and additional </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:1